      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span at least two load configurations or boundary condition variants to demonstrate robustness. Gradation 3 requires multi-condition coverage.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration only. No additional load angle or offset distance variants were included in this validation activity. Achieved Gradation 2 (single well-characterized condition). This factor is below required level; risk accepted given direct correspondence between test configuration and COU loading scenario and the availability of experimental replication across two laboratories."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material, boundary conditions) demonstrably equivalent to physical test specimen parameters within documented tolerances. Gradation 3 requires measured correspondence with quantified discrepancy.",
      "rationale": "CMM measurements of each test construct used to individualize corresponding FEA model geometry. Material properties matched to production lot coupon data. Boundary condition equivalency (fixture stiffness, load application point) verified by comparison of load-displacement curves in the linear elastic regime. Maximum input discrepancy between physical and virtual specimen: 1.4% on rod diameter."
    },
    {
