  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required gradation levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3; risk accepted given the direct correspondence of the single validated configuration to the COU loading scenario and the multi-laboratory experimental replication. All three QoIs satisfy the quantitative acceptance criterion (E/uval < 1.96) and the 10% mean absolute percent difference bound. Uncertainty quantification performed across material property and geometric tolerance distributions; a screening sensitivity study documented in the UQ report narrative confirms yield strength and rod diameter as dominant input drivers. Overall credibility is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion. Model accepted for use in the COU.",
